sven ottke (born 3 june 1967) is a german former professional boxer who competed from 1997 to 2004. he held the ibf super-middleweight title from 1998 to 2004, and the wba (super) super-middleweight title from 2003 to 2004. he made 21 successful title defences, and was the third european boxer to retire as an undefeated world champion, after terry marsh and michael loewe; joe calzaghe later became the fourth. as an amateur, ottke won a bronze medal in the middleweight division at the 1989 world amateur boxing championships.